Syntax: shieldblock

Prepares an active shield block, improving your armor class for a period
of combat rounds. Shieldblock is a Warrior-line finisher skill: it can only
be activated when your combo counter has reached the required threshold
during active combat.

Effects when activated:
  - Grants a -1 AC (armor class) bonus for (combo_count - 3) combat rounds.
    Lower AC makes you harder to hit.
  - The combo counter is reset after activation.
  - Skill proficiency improves on successful use.

You must be using a shield to get full benefit from this skill. Shieldblock
is available to Warden, Knight, Paladin, Crusader, and other classes that
train defensive techniques.

Requirements:
  - Must be in combat.
  - Requires a valid finisher combo count (combo threshold met).
  - Must have the skill learned.

See also: shelp shieldblock chiblock riposte parry dodge
